t is the GST registration threshold in Singapore?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The GST registration threshold in Singapore is S$1 million in taxable turnover over a 12-month period. Once your taxable turnover exceeds this threshold, you are required to register for GST within 30 days."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between the retrospective and prospective GST tests?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The retrospective test looks at whether your taxable turnover in the past 12 calendar months has exceeded S$1 million. The prospective test applies when you have reasonable grounds to expect your taxable turnover in the next 12 months will exceed S$1 million. Either test can trigger mandatory registration."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens if you miss the GST registration deadline?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"IRAS can backdate your GST registration and make you liable for GST you should have charged from the required date, even if you did not collect it. Financial penalties also apply."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you register for GST voluntarily in Singapore?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Businesses below the S$1 million threshold can apply to IRAS for voluntary GST registration. This makes sense if you have mainly GST-registered business customers and significant input tax to claim."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the current GST rate in Singapore?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The GST rate in Singapore is 9% from 1 January 2024."}}]},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://accountantforsmallbusiness.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"GST Registration Calculator Singapore 2026","item":"https://accountantforsmallbusiness.com/gst-registration-calculator-singapore/"}]}]}
